;: \u0026quot;The launch success rate may depend on many factors such as payload mass, orbit type, and so on. It may also depend on the location and proximities of a launch site, i.e., the initial position of rocket trajectories. Finding an optimal location for building a launch site certainly involves many factors and hopefully we could discover some of the factors by analyzing the existing launch site locations.\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {}","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;markdown\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;In the previous exploratory data analysis labs, you have visualized the SpaceX launch dataset using `matplotlib` and `seaborn` and discovered some preliminary correlations between the launch site and success rates. In this lab, you will be performing more interactive visual analytics using `Folium`.\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {}","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;markdown\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;## Objectives\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {}","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;markdown\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;This lab contains the following tasks:\\n\\n*   **TASK 1:** Mark all launch sites on a map\\n*   **TASK 2:** Mark the success/failed launches for each site on the map\\n*   **TASK 3:** Calculate the distances between a launch site to its proximities\\n\\nAfter completed the above tasks, you should be able to find some geographical patterns about launch sites.\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {}","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;markdown\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;Let\u0026#39;s first import required Python packages for this lab:\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {}","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;code\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;import piplite\\nawait piplite.install([\u0026#39;folium\u0026#39;])\\nawait piplite.install([\u0026#39;pandas\u0026#39;])\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {","        \u0026quot;trusted\u0026quot;: true","      },","      \u0026quot;outputs\u0026quot;: [],","      \u0026quot;execution_count\u0026quot;: 38","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;code\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;import folium\\nimport pandas as pd\\nprint(\u0026#39;Folium installed and imported!\u0026#39;)\\nprint(\u0026#39;pandas installed and imported!\u0026#39;)\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {","        \u0026quot;trusted\u0026quot;: true,","        \u0026quot;scrolled\u0026quot;: true","      },","      \u0026quot;outputs\u0026quot;: [","        {","          \u0026quot;name\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;stdout\u0026quot;,","          \u0026quot;text\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;Folium installed and imported!\\npandas installed and imported!\\n\u0026quot;,","          \u0026quot;output_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;stream\u0026quot;","        }","      ],","      \u0026quot;execution_count\u0026quot;: 39","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;code\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;# Import folium MarkerCluster plugin\\nfrom folium.plugins import MarkerCluster\\n# Import folium MousePosition plugin\\nfrom folium.plugins import MousePosition\\n# Import folium DivIcon plugin\\nfrom folium.features import DivIcon\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {","        \u0026quot;trusted\u0026quot;: true","      },","      \u0026quot;outputs\u0026quot;: [],","      \u0026quot;execution_count\u0026quot;: 40","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;markdown\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;If you need to refresh your memory about folium, you may download and refer to this previous folium lab:\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {}","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;markdown\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;[Generating Maps with Python](https://cf-courses-data.s3.us.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud/IBMDeveloperSkillsNetwork-DV0101EN-SkillsNetwork/labs/v4/DV0101EN-Exercise-Generating-Maps-in-Python.ipynb)\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {}","    },","    {","      \u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;code\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;source\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;## Task 1: Mark all launch sites on a map\\n\\n# Calculate the mean latitude and longitude\\nnasa_coordinate = [spacex_df[\u0026#39;Lat\u0026#39;].mean(), spacex_df[\u0026#39;Long\u0026#39;].mean()]\\n\\n# Create the map\\nsite_map = folium.Map(\\n    location=nasa_coordinate,\\n    zoom_start=4\\n)\\n\\nsite_map\\n# Add a marker cluster\\nmarker_cluster = MarkerCluster().add_to(site_map)\\n\\n# Loop through each launch site and add a marker\\nfor index, record in spacex_df.iterrows():\\n    folium.CircleMarker(\\n        location=[record[\u0026#39;Lat\u0026#39;], record[\u0026#39;Long\u0026#39;]],\\n        radius=5,\\n        color=\u0026#39;blue\u0026#39;,\\n        fill=True,\\n        fill_color=\u0026#39;blue\u0026#39;,\\n        fill_opacity=0.6,\\n        popup=record[\u0026#39;Launch Site\u0026#39;]\\n    ).add_to(marker_cluster)\\nsite_map\\n\u0026quot;,","      \u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;: {","        \u0026quot;trusted\u0026quot;: true","      },","      \u0026quot;outputs\u0026quot;: [","        {","          \u0026quot;execution_count\u0026quot;: 41,","          \u0026quot;output_type\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;execute_result\u0026quot;,","          \u0026quot;data\u0026quot;: {","            \u0026quot;text/plain\u0026quot;: \u0026qu